ty shading/Republican}} | Republican\n|1977&ndash;1991\n|-\n|42\n|[[George H. Ryan]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Republican\n|January 10, 1983\n|January 14, 1991\n|[[James R. Thompson]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Republican\n|1977&ndash;1991\n|-\n|43\n|[[Robert W. Kustra|Bob Kustra]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Republican\n|January 14, 1991\n|July 1, 1998<br />Resigned\n|[[Jim Edgar|James Edgar]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Republican\n|1991&ndash;1999\n|-\n|\n|Office vacant\n|\n|July 1, 1998\n|January 11, 1999\n|[[Jim Edgar|James Edgar]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Republican\n|1991&ndash;1999\n|-\n|44\n|[[Corinne Wood]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Republican\n|January 11, 1999\n|January 13, 2003\n|[[George Ryan|George H. Ryan]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Republican\n|1999&ndash;2003\n|-\n|45\n|[[Pat Quinn (politician)|Pat Quinn]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Democratic\n|January 13, 2003\n|January 29, 2009<br />Succeeded Blagojevich\n|[[Rod Blagojevich|Rod R. Blagojevich]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Democratic\n|2003&ndash;2009\n|- \n|\n|Office vacant\n|\n|January 29, 2009\n|January 10, 2011\n|[[Pat Quinn (politician)|Pat Quinn]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Democratic\n|2009&ndash;2011\n|-\n|46\n|[[Sheila Simon]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Democratic\n|January 10, 2011\n|January 12, 2015\n|[[Pat Quinn (politician)|Pat Quinn]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Democratic\n|2011&ndash;2015\n|-\n|47\n|[[Evelyn Sanguinetti]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Republican\n|January 12, 2015\n|January 14, 2019\n|[[Bruce Rauner]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Republican\n|2015&ndash;2019\n|-\n|48\n|[[Juliana Stratton]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Democratic\n|January 14, 2019\n|Incumbent\n|[[J.B. Pritzker]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Democratic\n|2019&ndash;Present\n|-\n|}\n\n==Living former lieutenant governors of Illinois==\n{{As of|2019|1}}, there are eight former lieutenant governors of Illinois who are living, the oldest lieutenant governor of Illinois being [[George Ryan]] (served 1983&ndash;1991, born 1934). The most recent death of a former lieutenant governor of Illinois was that of [[Paul Simon (politician)|Paul Simon]] (served 1969&ndash;1973, born 1928), on December 9, 2003. He is also the most recent serving lieutenant governor of Illinois to die.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Lt. governor!!Lt. gubernatorial term!!Date of birth (and age)\n|-\n|[[Neil Hartigan]]\n|1973&ndash;1977\n|{{birth date and age|mf=yes|1938|5|4}}\n|-\n|[[Dave O'Neal]]\n|1977&ndash;1981\n|{{birth date and age|mf=yes|1937|1|24}}\n|-\n|[[George Ryan]]\n|1983&ndash;1991\n|{{birth date and age|mf=yes|1934|2|24}}\n|-\n|[[Robert W. Kustra|Bob Kustra]]\n|1991&ndash;1998\n|{{birth date and age|mf=yes|1943|3|21}}\n|-\n|[[Corinne Wood]]\n|1999&ndash;2003\n|{{birth date and age|mf=yes|1954|5|28}}\n|-\n|[[Pat Quinn (politician)|Pat Quinn]]\n|2003&ndash;2009\n|{{birth date and age|mf=yes|1948|12|16}}\n|-\n|[[Sheila Simon]]\n|2011&ndash;2015\n|{{birth date and age|mf=yes|1961|3|13}}\n|-\n|[[Evelyn Sanguinetti]]\n|2015\u20132019\n|{{birth date and age|mf=yes|1970|11|12}}\n|}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070711093757/http://www.cyberdriveillinois.com/publications/illinois_bluebook/2005_2006/state_local_government_facts/roster.pdf Roster of elected officials, Illinois 2005-2006 Blue Book]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070616135408/http://www.sos.state.il.us/publications/illinois_bluebook/2005_2006/history_election_results/history.pdf Illinois 2005-2006 Blue Book, Illinois Governor mini-bios]\n\n{{Lists of lieutenant governors by U.S. state}}\n{{Governors of Illinois |expanded=Lt. Governors}}\n{{Illinois}}\n{{Illinois year nav}}\n\n[[Category:Lieutenant Governors of Illinois|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of Illinois politicians|Lieutenant Governors]]\n[[Category:Lists of state lieutenant governors of the United States|Illinois]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment"